==English==

===Etymology===
From {{der|en|la|nū̆cleus}}, a contraction of the adjective {{m|la|nuculeus}}, masculine of feminine {{m|la|nuculea|t=pertaining to a small nut}} from {{m|la|nucula}} + adjectival suffix {{m|la|[[-eus]], -ea, -eum}}. The {{cog|la|nucula}} + {{m|la|-āris}} adds up to {{m|la|nuculāris}}, a term that in English becomes {{m|en|nucular}}; the {{cog|la|nuculea}} + {{m|la|-āris}}, becomes {{cog|la|nuculeāris|t=relative to what pertains to small nut}}, later contracted into ''nuclear''. Compare {{m|en|muscle}} and {{cog|la|mūsculus}}; {{m|en|muscular}} and {{m|la|mūsculāris}}.

